================= PYTHON FUNCTIONS + METHODS =================
FUNCTIONS & METHODS (PYTHON)
|
|-- A) THE CORE DEFINITIONS (BURN THIS INTO BRAIN)
|    |-- FUNCTION = REUSABLE CODE BLOCK, CALLED DIRECTLY
|    |     |-- CALL: f(x)
|    |-- METHOD = FUNCTION ATTACHED TO AN OBJECT/CLASS
|    |     |-- CALL: obj.m(x)
|    |-- SIMPLE RULE
|         |-- IF YOU SEE DOT (.) BEFORE NAME → METHOD
|         |-- IF NO DOT → FUNCTION (OR VARIABLE HOLDING A FUNCTION)
|
|-- B) HOW CALLING REALLY WORKS (THE “SECRET” THAT REMOVES CONFUSION)
|    |-- obj.m(x) IS BASICALLY:
|    |     |-- type(obj).m(obj, x)   (obj IS PASSED AS FIRST ARGUMENT)
|    |-- THAT FIRST ARGUMENT NAME IS:
|    |     |-- self (INSTANCE METHOD)
|    |     |-- cls  (CLASS METHOD)
|
|-- C) FUNCTIONS (USER-DEFINED) — COMPLETE
|    |
|    |-- C1) DEFINE + CALL
|    |     |-- def f(params):
|    |     |--     body
|    |     |--     return value
|    |
|    |-- C2) RETURN RULES (MOST IMPORTANT)
|    |     |-- return x        -> RETURNS x
|    |     |-- return          -> RETURNS None
|    |     |-- no return       -> RETURNS None
|    |     |-- return a, b     -> RETURNS (a, b)  (TUPLE)
|    |
|    |-- C3) PARAMETERS vs ARGUMENTS
|    |     |-- PARAMETER: NAME INSIDE def(...)
|    |     |-- ARGUMENT: VALUE YOU PASS WHILE CALLING
|    |
|    |-- C4) ALL PARAMETER TYPES (ULTRA IMPORTANT)
|    |     |
|    |     |-- POSITIONAL PARAMETERS
|    |     |     |-- def f(a,b): ...
|    |     |     |-- f(10,20)
|    |     |
|    |     |-- KEYWORD ARGUMENTS
|    |     |     |-- f(a=10,b=20)
|    |     |
|    |     |-- DEFAULT PARAMETERS
|    |     |     |-- def f(a, b=5)
|    |     |     |-- DEFAULTS EVALUATE ONCE (MUTABLE DEFAULT TRAP)
|    |     |
|    |     |-- *args (VARIADIC POSITIONAL)
|    |     |     |-- def f(*args): args IS A TUPLE
|    |     |
|    |     |-- **kwargs (VARIADIC KEYWORD)
|    |     |     |-- def f(**kwargs): kwargs IS A DICT
|    |     |
|    |     |-- KEYWORD-ONLY PARAMETERS
|    |     |     |-- def f(a, *, b, c=0):  b & c MUST BE NAMED
|    |     |
|    |     |-- POSITIONAL-ONLY (ADVANCED)
|    |           |-- def f(a, b, /, c):  a,b MUST BE POSITIONAL
|    |
|    |-- C5) ARGUMENT PASSING RULES (NEVER FORGET)
|    |     |-- POSITIONAL FIRST, THEN KEYWORD
|    |     |-- ONE PARAMETER CANNOT RECEIVE TWO VALUES
|    |     |-- ORDER OF UNPACKING IN CALLS
|    |           |-- f(*iterable, **dict)
|    |
|    |-- C6) PACKING vs UNPACKING (THE SUPERPOWER)
|    |     |-- PACKING
|    |     |     |-- def f(*args, **kwargs)
|    |     |-- UNPACKING
|    |     |     |-- f(*L)    -> SPLIT LIST INTO POSITIONAL
|    |     |     |-- f(**D)   -> SPLIT DICT INTO KEYWORDS
|    |     |-- MULTI UNPACK (ADVANCED)
|    |           |-- f(*L1, *L2)
|    |           |-- f(**D1, **D2)  (NEWER PYTHON)
|    |
|    |-- C7) SCOPE (LEGB RULE) — SOURCE OF MANY DOUBTS
|    |     |-- L: LOCAL (INSIDE FUNCTION)
|    |     |-- E: ENCLOSING (NESTED OUTER FUNCTION)
|    |     |-- G: GLOBAL (MODULE LEVEL)
|    |     |-- B: BUILT-IN (len, print, ...)
|    |     |-- global   -> MODIFY GLOBAL VARIABLE
|    |     |-- nonlocal -> MODIFY ENCLOSING VARIABLE
|    |
|    |-- C8) MUTABILITY + PASSING (THE #1 REAL BUG SOURCE)
|    |     |-- PYTHON PASSES OBJECT REFERENCES (CALL-BY-SHARING)
|    |     |-- MUTABLE (list, dict, set) CAN BE MODIFIED IN FUNCTION
|    |     |-- IMMUTABLE (int, str, tuple) CAN’T BE CHANGED IN PLACE
|    |     |-- SAFE PATTERN:
|    |           |-- NEVER MODIFY INPUT LIST UNLESS SPECIFIED
|    |           |-- MAKE COPY WHEN NEEDED: new = old.copy()
|    |
|    |-- C9) DOCSTRINGS + TYPE HINTS (PRO LEVEL)
|    |     |-- """EXPLAINS WHAT FUNCTION DOES"""
|    |     |-- def f(x: int) -> int:
|    |     |-- MAKES CODE READABLE + IDE HELP
|    |
|    |-- C10) LAMBDA (ANONYMOUS FUNCTION)
|    |     |-- lambda x: x*x
|    |     |-- MOSTLY USED FOR key= IN sort/sorted
|    |
|    |-- C11) HIGHER-ORDER FUNCTIONS (FUNCTIONS AS DATA)
|    |     |-- PASS FUNCTION: map(f, items)
|    |     |-- RETURN FUNCTION: def outer(): return inner
|    |
|    |-- C12) RECURSION (ADVANCED LOGIC)
|    |     |-- BASE CASE (STOP)
|    |     |-- RECURSIVE CASE (CALL SELF)
|    |     |-- STACK DEPTH LIMIT
|
|-- D) METHODS — COMPLETE (OBJECT SIDE)
|    |
|    |-- D1) WHAT IS A METHOD REALLY?
|    |     |-- FUNCTION INSIDE CLASS
|    |     |-- CALLED USING OBJECT: obj.m(...)
|    |
|    |-- D2) 3 MAIN METHOD TYPES (MUST KNOW)
|    |     |
|    |     |-- INSTANCE METHOD (MOST COMMON)
|    |     |     |-- def m(self, ...): ...
|    |     |     |-- USES/CHANGES OBJECT STATE
|    |     |
|    |     |-- CLASS METHOD
|    |     |     |-- @classmethod
|    |     |     |-- def m(cls, ...): ...
|    |     |     |-- ALTERNATE CONSTRUCTORS, FACTORIES
|    |     |
|    |     |-- STATIC METHOD
|    |           |-- @staticmethod
|    |           |-- def m(...): ...
|    |           |-- UTILITY FUNCTION KEPT INSIDE CLASS NAMESPACE
|
|    |-- D3) MAGIC / DUNDER METHODS (PRO LEVEL)
|    |     |-- __init__     (CONSTRUCTOR)
|    |     |-- __str__      (PRINTING)
|    |     |-- __repr__     (DEBUG VIEW)
|    |     |-- __len__      (len(obj))
|    |     |-- __iter__     (for x in obj)
|    |     |-- __getitem__  (obj[i])
|    |     |-- __setitem__  (obj[i]=x)
|    |     |-- __contains__ (x in obj)
|    |     |-- __call__     (obj() LIKE FUNCTION)
|
|-- E) BUILT-IN FUNCTIONS VS METHODS (THE COMMON CONFUSION)
|    |
|    |-- BUILT-IN FUNCTIONS (NO DOT)
|    |     |-- len(L), sum(L), min(L), max(L)
|    |     |-- sorted(L)  -> RETURNS NEW LIST
|    |     |-- type(x), isinstance(x, T)
|    |
|    |-- COMMON “FUNCTION vs METHOD” PAIRS (MEMORIZE)
|          |-- sorted(L)    vs  L.sort()
|          |-- reversed(L)  vs  L.reverse()
|          |-- str(x)       vs  x.__str__() (INTERNAL)
|
|-- F) MOST IMPORTANT METHOD FAMILIES (REAL-LIFE DAILY)
|    |
|    |-- LIST METHODS
|    |     |-- append, extend, insert
|    |     |-- pop, remove, clear
|    |     |-- sort, reverse, copy
|    |
|    |-- STRING METHODS (TEXT WORK)
|    |     |-- lower/upper/title
|    |     |-- strip/lstrip/rstrip
|    |     |-- replace
|    |     |-- split / rsplit
|    |     |-- join
|    |     |-- find / index
|    |     |-- startswith/endswith
|    |
|    |-- DICT METHODS (DATA STRUCTURE KING)
|    |     |-- get (SAFE ACCESS)
|    |     |-- keys, values, items
|    |     |-- update
|    |     |-- pop, popitem, clear
|    |     |-- setdefault
|    |
|    |-- SET METHODS (UNIQUE + FAST MEMBERSHIP)
|          |-- add, update
|          |-- remove, discard, pop
|          |-- union, intersection, difference
|
|-- G) ADVANCED FUNCTION TOOLS (PRO LEVEL FEATURES)
|    |
|    |-- G1) DECORATORS (@something)
|    |     |-- WRAP FUNCTION TO ADD EXTRA BEHAVIOR
|    |     |-- USE CASES: LOGGING, TIMING, AUTH, CACHING
|    |
|    |-- G2) GENERATORS (yield)
|    |     |-- LAZY OUTPUT (MEMORY SAVING)
|    |     |-- FOR STREAMING FILES / BIG DATA
|    |
|    |-- G3) ITERATORS + ITERABLES
|    |     |-- iterable: can be looped
|    |     |-- iterator: gives next() until StopIteration
|    |
|    |-- G4) PARTIAL FUNCTIONS (ADVANCED)
|    |     |-- fix some arguments, create new function
|    |
|    |-- G5) ASYNC FUNCTIONS
|          |-- async def, await (I/O concurrency)
|
|-- H) DESIGN PRINCIPLES (REAL-WORLD CLEAN CODE)
|    |-- SINGLE RESPONSIBILITY: ONE JOB PER FUNCTION
|    |-- PURE FUNCTIONS PREFERRED (EASY TESTING)
|    |-- SEPARATE I/O FROM LOGIC
|    |-- NAME CLEARLY (verb_noun style)
|    |-- RETURN VALUES INSTEAD OF PRINTING
|    |-- VALIDATE INPUTS, RAISE CLEAN ERRORS
|
|-- I) REAL-WORLD PIPELINES (WHERE FUNCTIONS + METHODS WIN)
|    |-- DATA CLEANING
|    |     |-- read -> parse -> clean -> validate -> transform -> export
|    |-- API PROCESSING
|    |     |-- list of dicts -> filter -> map -> sort -> aggregate
|    |-- AUTOMATION
|    |     |-- scan folders -> filter files -> rename -> report
|    |-- CLI PROGRAMS
|          |-- main() handles input/output
|          |-- helper functions handle logic
|
|-- J) DEBUGGING + MASTERY CHECKLIST (IF YES = YOU OWN IT)
|    |-- CAN EXPLAIN: obj.m(x) PASSES obj AS self
|    |-- CAN CHOOSE: sorted(L) VS L.sort() CORRECTLY
|    |-- CAN USE: default + keyword + *args + **kwargs
|    |-- CAN APPLY: UNPACKING (*list, **dict) WITHOUT ERRORS
|    |-- CAN EXPLAIN: LEGB + global + nonlocal
|    |-- CAN AVOID: MUTABLE DEFAULT ARGUMENT BUG
|    |-- CAN BUILD: CLEAN FUNCTIONS (LOGIC SEPARATE FROM I/O)
|    |-- CAN READ: help(), dir(), DOCSTRINGS
|    |-- CAN USE: DECORATORS / GENERATORS WHEN NEEDED
|
===========================================================================================
